1
00:00:00,467 --> 00:00:03,267
<i>[NARRATOR] Alchemy...
the science of understanding,</i>

2
00:00:03,267 --> 00:00:05,700
<i>deconstructing, and
reconstructing matter...</i>

3
00:00:05,700 --> 00:00:08,767
<i>However, it is not
an all-powerful art.</i>

4
00:00:08,767 --> 00:00:11,667
<i>It is impossible to create
something out of nothing.</i>

5
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:13,534
<i>If one wishes to
obtain something,</i>

6
00:00:13,534 --> 00:00:16,167
<i>something of equal value
must be given.</i>

7
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:18,600
<i>This is the Law of
Equivalent Exchange--</i>

8
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:20,567
<i>the basis of all alchemy...</i>

9
00:00:20,567 --> 00:00:21,767
<i>In accordance with this law,</i>

10
00:00:21,767 --> 00:00:23,767
<i>there is a taboo
among alchemists.</i>

11
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:26,267
<i>Human transmutation
is strictly forbidden.</i>

12
00:00:26,267 --> 00:00:29,434
<i>For what could equal
the value of a human soul?</i>

13
00:02:02,991 --> 00:02:04,116
<i>[NARRATOR] In order
to learn more about</i>

14
00:02:04,116 --> 00:02:05,271
<i>the field of bio alchemy,</i>

15
00:02:05,271 --> 00:02:07,637
<i>Ed and Al visited the
home of Shou Tucker,</i>

16
00:02:07,637 --> 00:02:09,671
<i>the Sewing Life Alchemist...</i>

17
00:02:09,671 --> 00:02:10,971
There, they befriended Tucker's

18
00:02:10,971 --> 00:02:14,237
<i>young daughter Nina
and her dog Alexander...</i>

19
00:02:14,237 --> 00:02:16,337
<i>The day of Tucker's
annual State Alchemist</i>

20
00:02:16,337 --> 00:02:18,837
<i>certification assessment
was drawing near.</i>

21
00:02:18,837 --> 00:02:22,371
<i>In his desperation to pass,
he used Nina and Alexander</i>

22
00:02:22,371 --> 00:02:24,537
<i>to create a talking chimera.</i>

23
00:02:24,537 --> 00:02:27,404
<i>Knowing that nothing he did
could ever change Nina back,</i>

24
00:02:27,404 --> 00:02:30,737
<i>Ed was grief-stricken
at his own powerlessness.</i>

25
00:02:37,904 --> 00:02:40,837
[ED (AGE 5)]
Hey, Mom...! Mom!

26
00:02:40,837 --> 00:02:43,604
What do you
have there, Ed?

27
00:02:43,604 --> 00:02:46,771
It's a present!
I transmuted it!

28
00:02:46,771 --> 00:02:50,704
[TRISHA] You did...? You're
your father's son, all right.

29
00:02:50,704 --> 00:02:51,771
Thank you very much.

30
00:02:51,771 --> 00:02:53,637
That's an amazing
thing you did...

31
00:02:53,637 --> 00:02:57,204
Creating something as
neat as this takes talent.

32
00:02:57,204 --> 00:02:58,637
[TRISHA]
But...

33
00:03:00,604 --> 00:03:02,304
[TRISHA (CHIMERA)]
If you can do that...

34
00:03:02,304 --> 00:03:05,804
why couldn't you
make Mommy better, Ed?

35
00:03:05,804 --> 00:03:07,571
[NINA]
Big brother!

36
00:03:08,937 --> 00:03:10,537
Let's play!

37
00:03:15,704 --> 00:03:18,671
[AL]
Brother, are you all right...?

38
00:03:18,671 --> 00:03:20,704
You were dreaming.

39
00:03:27,671 --> 00:03:29,671
[RAIN HITTING THE GROUND]

40
00:03:36,671 --> 00:03:38,271
What's the matter,
you two...?

41
00:03:38,271 --> 00:03:40,237
You're up awfully early.

42
00:03:40,237 --> 00:03:42,937
We... need to know...

43
00:03:42,937 --> 00:03:46,337
[ED] What's going to happen
to Tucker and Nina?

44
00:03:47,304 --> 00:03:49,904
Mr. Tucker was scheduled to be
stripped of his certification

45
00:03:49,904 --> 00:03:52,771
and stand trial
for what he did to Nina.

46
00:03:52,771 --> 00:03:54,604
[HAWKEYE]
But... they're both dead.

47
00:03:54,604 --> 00:03:55,904
[AL]
Dead?!

48
00:03:57,537 --> 00:03:58,604
[HAWKEYE] You'll
find out anyway, so

49
00:03:58,604 --> 00:04:00,371
I might as well tell you...

50
00:04:00,371 --> 00:04:01,871
They've been murdered.

51
00:04:01,871 --> 00:04:04,404
They... How? By who?!

52
00:04:04,404 --> 00:04:05,504
We don't know.

53
00:04:05,504 --> 00:04:07,904
[HAWKEYE] I was just
heading over to the scene now.

54
00:04:07,904 --> 00:04:09,504
[AL]
We're coming with you.

55
00:04:09,504 --> 00:04:10,371
[HAWKEYE]
No.

56
00:04:10,371 --> 00:04:11,937
Why not?!

57
00:04:13,437 --> 00:04:15,337
You don't need to see this.

58
00:04:15,337 --> 00:04:17,371
[RAIN POURING]

59
00:04:18,604 --> 00:04:20,571
He's always
one step ahead of us.

60
00:04:20,571 --> 00:04:22,237
We'd better catch up
to him quickly,

61
00:04:22,237 --> 00:04:24,804
because the way
things are going...

62
00:04:25,804 --> 00:04:28,604
[ROY] You sound as though
you were expecting this...

63
00:04:28,604 --> 00:04:30,371
Fill me in.

64
00:04:33,904 --> 00:04:36,771
[CORNELLO] God has given us
a great trial, my children...!

65
00:04:36,771 --> 00:04:39,371
Wicked heathens have
spread insidious rumors,

66
00:04:39,371 --> 00:04:40,937
trying to shake our faith...

67
00:04:40,937 --> 00:04:44,737
and now the military
seeks to oppress us!

68
00:04:44,737 --> 00:04:46,937
But we must hold
tight to our faith!

69
00:04:46,937 --> 00:04:49,737
The time has come to
rise up, weapon in hand,

70
00:04:49,737 --> 00:04:52,637
and fight in the name
of the great god Leto!

71
00:04:52,637 --> 00:04:55,771
[MAN A] Yeah...! We fight under
the protection of Leto!

72
00:04:55,771 --> 00:04:57,971
Down with heathens and heresy!

73
00:04:57,971 --> 00:04:59,804
[MAN C]
No...! Don't be fooled!

74
00:04:59,804 --> 00:05:01,504
[MAN D] That man speaks
nothing but lies!

75
00:05:01,504 --> 00:05:02,537
Can't you see that?

76
00:05:02,537 --> 00:05:03,804
[MAN E]
Hold your tongue!

77
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:06,404
[MAN F] We aren't pawns of the
heathens like all of you are!

78
00:05:06,404 --> 00:05:07,404
[LUST LAUGHS]

79
00:05:07,404 --> 00:05:10,571
Human foolishness
never ceases to amaze me.

80
00:05:10,571 --> 00:05:11,571
[GLASS BREAKING]

81
00:05:11,571 --> 00:05:13,604
[CROWD FIGHTING AND RIOTING]

82
00:05:15,837 --> 00:05:17,571
[CHILD CRYING]

83
00:05:20,871 --> 00:05:23,271
[LUST] Wouldn't
you agree, Gluttony?

84
00:05:23,271 --> 00:05:24,671
[GLUTTONY]
Fools, all of 'em!

85
00:05:24,671 --> 00:05:27,371
Fools indeed. Sad but true.

86
00:05:27,371 --> 00:05:29,371
Well-well,
if it isn't the father.

87
00:05:29,371 --> 00:05:30,471
Yeah, "Father."

88
00:05:30,471 --> 00:05:33,537
[LUST] Sorry to have put
you to all of this trouble.

89
00:05:33,537 --> 00:05:35,437
As soon as we have
everything handled here,

90
00:05:35,437 --> 00:05:39,304
I have my own responsibilities
I need to get back to.

91
00:05:39,304 --> 00:05:41,837
The Fullmetal boy's
interference was irritating,

92
00:05:41,837 --> 00:05:44,771
but at least we were able
to make it work in our favor.

93
00:05:44,771 --> 00:05:47,504
[LUST] Looks like we'll finish
up ahead of schedule.

94
00:05:47,504 --> 00:05:49,271
[CORNELLO]
Manipulate a little information,

95
00:05:49,271 --> 00:05:51,304
spout some empty
rhetoric to the believers,

96
00:05:51,304 --> 00:05:54,204
and you have a fine
recipe for instant violence...

97
00:05:54,204 --> 00:05:57,571
Humans are
such simple creatures.

98
00:05:57,571 --> 00:05:59,804
[LUST] Bloodshed gives way
to more bloodshed,

99
00:05:59,804 --> 00:06:01,771
hatred breeds more hatred,

100
00:06:01,771 --> 00:06:04,504
until all of the violence
soaks into the land,

101
00:06:04,504 --> 00:06:07,304
carving rivers of blood.

102
00:06:07,304 --> 00:06:09,371
And no matter how
many times it happens,

103
00:06:09,371 --> 00:06:10,604
they never learn...

104
00:06:10,604 --> 00:06:12,471
The human race
is made up of violent,

105
00:06:12,471 --> 00:06:14,404
miserable fools.

106
00:06:14,404 --> 00:06:17,304
[CORNELLO] Who seem more than
willing to play into our hands.

107
00:06:17,304 --> 00:06:18,637
[LUST SMIRKS]

108
00:06:18,637 --> 00:06:21,237
[GLUTTONY] Are lots
of people gonna die again?

109
00:06:21,237 --> 00:06:22,704
[LUST] Yes, they will.

110
00:06:22,704 --> 00:06:24,904
Ooh! Can I eat all
of them after they die?

111
00:06:24,904 --> 00:06:26,704
[LUST]
No, you may not.

112
00:06:26,704 --> 00:06:27,604
[LUST]
By the way Envy,

113
00:06:27,604 --> 00:06:29,871
could you lose the
old man costume...?

114
00:06:29,871 --> 00:06:31,537
It's rather unattractive.

115
00:06:31,537 --> 00:06:32,504
Come on,

116
00:06:32,504 --> 00:06:34,771
I was just staying in character.

117
00:06:34,771 --> 00:06:36,771
But if you insist...

118
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:39,671
This time around I'll go
with a younger, cuter model.

119
00:06:39,671 --> 00:06:41,704
What do ya say?

120
00:06:42,271 --> 00:06:43,104
[ENVY CHUCKLES]

121
00:06:43,104 --> 00:06:43,904
[ASSISTANT PASTOR
REACTS WITH SHOCK]

122
00:06:43,904 --> 00:06:46,404
[ASSISTANT PASTOR]
A... a monster!

123
00:06:46,404 --> 00:06:47,471
[ASSISTANT PASTOR]
What's going on here...?

124
00:06:47,471 --> 00:06:48,537
What have you done...?!

125
00:06:48,537 --> 00:06:50,804
What have you done
with the real Father Cornello?!

126
00:06:50,804 --> 00:06:52,204
It's your call.

127
00:06:52,204 --> 00:06:53,504
He said I was a monster.

128
00:06:53,504 --> 00:06:55,304
I think that's
quite rude, don't you?

129
00:06:55,304 --> 00:06:57,737
Can I eat him? Can I?

130
00:07:00,637 --> 00:07:02,204
Oh, hey, did ya
hear the news...?

131
00:07:02,204 --> 00:07:04,437
Shou Tucker, that
alchemist in East City...

132
00:07:04,437 --> 00:07:05,504
he's dead.

133
00:07:05,504 --> 00:07:06,571
[LUST] Tucker...?

134
00:07:06,571 --> 00:07:09,537
Why should we care about a
little nothing like him?

135
00:07:09,537 --> 00:07:13,237
Because it was him who
was responsible for the murder.

136
00:07:13,237 --> 00:07:14,404
Speaking of East City,

137
00:07:14,404 --> 00:07:16,904
isn't that where the Flame
Colonel's staying right now?

138
00:07:16,904 --> 00:07:18,004
[ENVY]
Yeah...

139
00:07:18,004 --> 00:07:20,604
...and apparently the
Fullmetal brat's there too.

140
00:07:20,604 --> 00:07:22,371
Oh, is he?

141
00:07:22,371 --> 00:07:24,504
[LUST] As furious as
I am that he interfered

142
00:07:24,504 --> 00:07:27,671
with our work here, we can't
very well let him die.

143
00:07:27,671 --> 00:07:30,271
He's an important sacrifice.

144
00:07:30,271 --> 00:07:32,671
Ooh! That was so yummy!

145
00:07:32,671 --> 00:07:35,671
[LUST] We'll find some way
of handling the situation.

146
00:07:35,671 --> 00:07:39,204
The other one we were speaking
of... what was his name?

147
00:07:43,462 --> 00:07:44,207
[ROY]
Scar?

148
00:07:44,207 --> 00:07:45,350
Because of his face?

149
00:07:45,350 --> 00:07:47,583
Yeah, we don't really know
anything else about him,

150
00:07:47,583 --> 00:07:49,117
so that's what
we're calling him.

151
00:07:49,117 --> 00:07:52,250
Our target is both
unidentified and elusive.

152
00:07:52,250 --> 00:07:54,217
The only information
we've been able to obtain

153
00:07:54,217 --> 00:07:56,917
about him is that he has a
large scar on his forehead.

154
00:07:56,917 --> 00:07:59,283
Yes, I've heard stories
about that man...

155
00:07:59,283 --> 00:08:01,683
That's who you're
trying to hunt down?

156
00:08:01,683 --> 00:08:04,250
[HUGHES] By order of the
military police command center.

157
00:08:04,250 --> 00:08:06,550
Meanwhile, all my
other work is piling up...

158
00:08:06,550 --> 00:08:08,250
Ugh, my head hurts.

159
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:10,583
[ARMSTRONG] He's killed
five people in Central,

160
00:08:10,583 --> 00:08:12,117
all State Alchemists...

161
00:08:12,117 --> 00:08:15,150
His body count
nationwide is up to ten.

162
00:08:15,150 --> 00:08:18,317
[HUGHES] Five days ago,
he took down old man Grand.

163
00:08:18,317 --> 00:08:20,217
The Brigadier General?

164
00:08:20,217 --> 00:08:23,250
[ROY] But-- he's an expert
in weapons transmutation!

165
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:26,217
That shows you how
dangerous this guy is.

166
00:08:26,217 --> 00:08:27,650
[HUGHES] You should
increase your escort

167
00:08:27,650 --> 00:08:28,850
and lay low for awhile.

168
00:08:28,850 --> 00:08:30,683
Nobody will blame you.

169
00:08:30,683 --> 00:08:33,083
[HUGHES] Please...
I'm asking as your friend...

170
00:08:33,083 --> 00:08:34,083
You and Tucker
are the only

171
00:08:34,083 --> 00:08:37,750
State Alchemists of
note in this area, right?

172
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:38,917
Oh no!

173
00:08:40,283 --> 00:08:43,050
[ED] I've been thinking
about this for a long time.

174
00:08:43,050 --> 00:08:44,683
We put all our trust
in alchemy,

175
00:08:44,683 --> 00:08:46,983
but in the end, what is it?

176
00:08:46,983 --> 00:08:49,717
"Alchemy is the science of
understanding the flow of matter

177
00:08:49,717 --> 00:08:52,883
and its laws...
the process of comprehension,

178
00:08:52,883 --> 00:08:55,117
deconstruction, and
reconstruction."

179
00:08:55,117 --> 00:08:56,250
"The world flows, too.

180
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:57,717
It must also follow laws.

181
00:08:57,717 --> 00:08:59,250
Everything circulates...

182
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:01,717
Even Death is a
part of that circulation.

183
00:09:01,717 --> 00:09:04,250
You must accept the flow."

184
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:07,917
Teacher sure drummed
that into our heads, didn't she?

185
00:09:08,917 --> 00:09:10,950
[ED]
I thought I understood it...

186
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:13,050
but I didn't
understand anything.

187
00:09:13,850 --> 00:09:16,117
[ED]
Mom proves that.

188
00:09:16,117 --> 00:09:18,617
Now here I am again,
trying desperately

189
00:09:18,617 --> 00:09:21,083
to figure out a way
to do the impossible.

190
00:09:21,083 --> 00:09:23,083
[NINA LAUGHS]

191
00:09:23,983 --> 00:09:26,183
I'm such a hopeless idiot...

192
00:09:26,183 --> 00:09:29,850
All this time, and I haven't
grown up one bit.

193
00:09:29,850 --> 00:09:31,917
I thought maybe the rain
would wash away some

194
00:09:31,917 --> 00:09:35,117
of this gloom
that's following me.

195
00:09:35,117 --> 00:09:37,217
[ED] But right now,
every drop that hits my face

196
00:09:37,217 --> 00:09:39,250
is even more depressing.

197
00:09:40,350 --> 00:09:42,683
[AL]
I don't even get that much.

198
00:09:42,683 --> 00:09:44,083
Without a body,

199
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:46,750
I can't feel the
rain hitting my face.

200
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,617
That's something I miss...

201
00:09:48,617 --> 00:09:50,117
All the time...

202
00:09:50,117 --> 00:09:53,083
I want to get my
body back soon Brother...

203
00:09:53,083 --> 00:09:55,117
I just want to be human again.

204
00:09:55,117 --> 00:09:57,583
Even if it means going
against the flow of the world

205
00:09:57,583 --> 00:10:00,050
and trying to do the impossible.

206
00:10:01,283 --> 00:10:02,217
You, boy, you're the

207
00:10:02,217 --> 00:10:05,050
Fullmetal Alchemist
Edward Elric, correct?

208
00:10:09,083 --> 00:10:10,550
[AL]
Brother!

209
00:10:10,817 --> 00:10:13,817
[BELLS CHIMING]

210
00:10:16,650 --> 00:10:18,250
[EXPLOSION]

211
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:20,850
What the hell is going on here?!

212
00:10:20,850 --> 00:10:22,883
[EXPLOSION]

213
00:10:27,883 --> 00:10:29,217
[ED THINKS]
Who is this guy...?

214
00:10:29,217 --> 00:10:30,583
What does he want...?

215
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:31,917
This is bad...

216
00:10:31,917 --> 00:10:33,583
This is really bad...

217
00:10:33,583 --> 00:10:35,150
I have to move... Now...

218
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:37,750
Let's go, Al! Run for it!

219
00:10:41,917 --> 00:10:43,917
[EXPLOSION]

220
00:10:45,617 --> 00:10:47,150
[SCAR]
No you don't.

221
00:10:49,183 --> 00:10:52,083
[STRUCTURE CRUMBLES]
[AL AND ED YELL IN PANIC]

222
00:10:52,083 --> 00:10:53,717
[AL]
Got you!

223
00:10:57,350 --> 00:10:59,550
[AL AND ED PANIC]

224
00:11:03,283 --> 00:11:08,650
Al, grab on!

225
00:11:08,650 --> 00:11:10,683
[AL AND ED YELL OUT
AS THEY TUMBLE]

226
00:11:14,150 --> 00:11:16,250
Damn it, what the hell is
this guy's problem...?!

227
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:18,583
Making enemies
isn't something that I--

228
00:11:18,583 --> 00:11:19,850
Well...

229
00:11:19,850 --> 00:11:21,750
I never really avoided it.

230
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:25,250
But there's no reason someone
should be trying to kill me!

231
00:11:34,883 --> 00:11:36,117
[ED]
Who are you, anyway...?

232
00:11:36,117 --> 00:11:38,183
Why are you after us?

233
00:11:38,183 --> 00:11:40,583
[SCAR] As long as there
are 'creators' like you

234
00:11:40,583 --> 00:11:43,817
in the world, there must
also be destroyers.

235
00:11:43,817 --> 00:11:46,283
Then it looks like
we're gonna have to fight.

236
00:11:52,283 --> 00:11:54,917
Gutsy one, aren't you...?

237
00:11:54,917 --> 00:11:56,217
But...

238
00:12:00,583 --> 00:12:01,850
Too slow.

239
00:12:03,317 --> 00:12:06,583
[METAL SHATTERING]

240
00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:08,250
Al!

241
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:10,583
<i>[NARRATOR]
Fullmetal Alchemist.</i>

242
00:12:14,130 --> 00:12:16,197
<i>[NARRATOR]
Fullmetal Alchemist.</i>

243
00:12:19,156 --> 00:12:21,308
[SCAR THINKS]
There's nothing inside!

244
00:12:21,308 --> 00:12:22,791
[ED]
You bastard!

245
00:12:24,415 --> 00:12:26,148
You're too slow!

246
00:12:29,115 --> 00:12:30,248
Damn it!

247
00:12:30,248 --> 00:12:32,048
An automail arm...

248
00:12:32,048 --> 00:12:33,682
Then that explains
why my attacks didn't

249
00:12:33,682 --> 00:12:36,082
do the damage I expected...

250
00:12:36,082 --> 00:12:37,615
Most unusual.

251
00:12:40,248 --> 00:12:41,748
[AL]
Brother... don't...!

252
00:12:41,748 --> 00:12:43,248
Just run away!

253
00:12:43,248 --> 00:12:44,448
You idiot!

254
00:12:44,448 --> 00:12:46,115
I'm not gonna
leave you behind, Al!

255
00:12:46,115 --> 00:12:48,348
You press your hands
together to make a ring,

256
00:12:48,348 --> 00:12:50,515
and then you perform transmutation...

257
00:12:50,515 --> 00:12:51,682
Now I see.

258
00:12:51,682 --> 00:12:53,715
[ED BELLOWS]

259
00:12:53,815 --> 00:12:54,848
[SCAR]
Then I will have to start

260
00:12:54,848 --> 00:12:59,282
by destroying this
abhorrent right arm of yours...

261
00:12:59,282 --> 00:13:00,582
Brother!

262
00:13:02,182 --> 00:13:05,182
[METAL HITTING THE GROUND]

263
00:13:08,482 --> 00:13:11,482
Now you will not be able
to use your heretic's alchemy.

264
00:13:15,682 --> 00:13:18,082
I will give you a
moment to pray to god.

265
00:13:18,082 --> 00:13:19,748
Brother...! Run away!

266
00:13:19,748 --> 00:13:21,082
Brother!

267
00:13:21,082 --> 00:13:22,615
[ED]
Unfortunately...

268
00:13:22,615 --> 00:13:26,715
there isn't any god
I'd like to pray to.

269
00:13:26,715 --> 00:13:30,082
Am I the only one
you're trying to kill today?

270
00:13:30,082 --> 00:13:33,248
Or are you going
after my brother Al, too?

271
00:13:33,248 --> 00:13:35,515
If he interferes,
I will eliminate him...

272
00:13:35,515 --> 00:13:36,648
but, Fullmetal Alchemist,

273
00:13:36,648 --> 00:13:40,148
you are the only one
who's receiving judgment today.

274
00:13:40,148 --> 00:13:41,748
You alone.

275
00:13:41,748 --> 00:13:43,348
[ED] Okay...

276
00:13:43,348 --> 00:13:45,482
In that case, I want your word.

277
00:13:45,482 --> 00:13:49,282
Promise me you
won't hurt my brother!

278
00:13:49,282 --> 00:13:50,348
Brother!

279
00:13:50,348 --> 00:13:52,315
I will keep that promise.

280
00:13:52,315 --> 00:13:55,082
[AL]
No, Brother, what
are you trying to do?

281
00:13:55,082 --> 00:13:57,648
What are you thinking...? Run!

282
00:13:57,648 --> 00:13:59,715
Get up and run!

283
00:13:59,715 --> 00:14:00,748
Stop...!

284
00:14:00,748 --> 00:14:02,348
Don't touch him!

285
00:14:02,348 --> 00:14:05,482
No...! No, you can't...!
Stop it!

286
00:14:05,482 --> 00:14:06,982
[GUN SHOT]

287
00:14:07,615 --> 00:14:09,148
[ROY]
That's enough!

288
00:14:09,148 --> 00:14:13,015
You won't be killing
anybody else today, Scar.

289
00:14:13,815 --> 00:14:16,148
I'm taking you into custody,
where you will answer

290
00:14:16,148 --> 00:14:19,015
for the murders of
at least ten State Alchemists.

291
00:14:19,015 --> 00:14:21,448
[SCAR] Alchemists alter things
from their natural form,

292
00:14:21,448 --> 00:14:23,248
perverting them
to something else,

293
00:14:23,248 --> 00:14:24,782
something grotesque...

294
00:14:24,782 --> 00:14:28,515
They profane God, the
true creator of all things...

295
00:14:28,515 --> 00:14:29,748
As an agent of God...

296
00:14:29,748 --> 00:14:32,348
I am here to hand
down his judgment.

297
00:14:32,348 --> 00:14:36,048
If you interfere, I will
eliminate you as well.

298
00:14:36,048 --> 00:14:38,615
Oh, is that right?

299
00:14:38,615 --> 00:14:40,182
[ROY]
You guys stay out of it.

300
00:14:40,182 --> 00:14:41,482
Colonel Mustang, sir!

301
00:14:41,482 --> 00:14:45,548
Colonel Mustang...
so this is the Flame Alchemist.

302
00:14:45,548 --> 00:14:48,415
[SCAR] Volunteering yourself
to receive judgment.

303
00:14:48,415 --> 00:14:50,548
This is truly an auspicious day!

304
00:14:50,548 --> 00:14:51,615
So you know who I am

305
00:14:51,615 --> 00:14:58,182
and you still want
to challenge me? Bad decision.

306
00:14:58,182 --> 00:15:01,215
[HAWKEYE FIRES WEAPONS]

307
00:15:02,515 --> 00:15:04,682
Hey, Hawkeye, what the
hell did you do that for?!

308
00:15:04,682 --> 00:15:05,748
You know as well as I do,

309
00:15:05,748 --> 00:15:07,415
you're useless
on rainy days.

310
00:15:07,415 --> 00:15:08,582
Please stay back.

311
00:15:08,582 --> 00:15:10,315
Oh yeah, I forgot.

312
00:15:10,315 --> 00:15:11,582
It's kinda hard
to get a spark going

313
00:15:11,582 --> 00:15:13,115
when it's raining, huh?

314
00:15:13,115 --> 00:15:14,015
It is fortunate that you

315
00:15:14,015 --> 00:15:15,682
can't create your
blasphemous flames,

316
00:15:15,682 --> 00:15:17,348
State Alchemist.

317
00:15:17,348 --> 00:15:19,682
For I will destroy all
who interfere with my mission,

318
00:15:19,682 --> 00:15:21,082
right here and now!

319
00:15:21,082 --> 00:15:23,182
[ARMSTRONG]
I'd like to see you try it.

320
00:15:23,182 --> 00:15:24,582
[IMPACT]

321
00:15:24,582 --> 00:15:25,715
A newcomer.

322
00:15:25,715 --> 00:15:28,448
[ARMSTRONG] You have to be
quick to avoid my fist...

323
00:15:28,448 --> 00:15:31,382
Not bad... not bad at all.

324
00:15:31,382 --> 00:15:33,615
You said you were
going to destroy us all...

325
00:15:33,615 --> 00:15:37,482
In that case... why don't
you start by defeating me?

326
00:15:37,482 --> 00:15:38,548
We'll see how you fare

327
00:15:38,548 --> 00:15:40,215
against the Strong
Arm Alchemist,

328
00:15:40,215 --> 00:15:42,282
Alex Louis Armstrong!

329
00:15:42,282 --> 00:15:44,215
Yet another State Alchemist...

330
00:15:44,215 --> 00:15:46,482
God is putting them
in my path for me.

331
00:15:46,482 --> 00:15:48,148
Not backing down...?

332
00:15:48,148 --> 00:15:49,082
In that case,

333
00:15:49,082 --> 00:15:52,048
your courage will earn
you a demonstration.

334
00:15:52,048 --> 00:15:53,482
I'll show you the
art of alchemy;

335
00:15:53,482 --> 00:15:54,348
that has been passed down

336
00:15:54,348 --> 00:15:57,115
the Armstrong
family for generations!

337
00:16:03,648 --> 00:16:04,648
Who is he?

338
00:16:04,648 --> 00:16:05,582
That's the same man

339
00:16:05,582 --> 00:16:07,982
who murdered Mr. Tucker
and his daughter.

340
00:16:11,115 --> 00:16:12,348
It's him!?

341
00:16:12,348 --> 00:16:13,682
Major, watch what you're doing!

342
00:16:13,682 --> 00:16:15,748
We don't want to
destroy the city, do we?

343
00:16:15,748 --> 00:16:17,048
What do you mean?!

344
00:16:17,048 --> 00:16:18,615
[ARMSTRONG]
Destruction and creation

345
00:16:18,615 --> 00:16:20,282
are two sides of the same coin.

346
00:16:20,282 --> 00:16:21,715
You must destroy to create.

347
00:16:21,715 --> 00:16:23,648
That is the law of the universe!

348
00:16:23,648 --> 00:16:25,115
Did he have to strip?

349
00:16:25,115 --> 00:16:27,482
Are you surprised?
He's clearly insane.

350
00:16:27,482 --> 00:16:29,548
(Hmph!) Non-alchemists
may fail to see the

351
00:16:29,548 --> 00:16:31,615
inherent truth of that statement...

352
00:16:31,615 --> 00:16:35,748
But we understand,
don't we, Scar?

353
00:16:35,748 --> 00:16:38,048
So this killer is
an alchemist, too?

354
00:16:38,048 --> 00:16:39,015
That's it...!

355
00:16:39,015 --> 00:16:41,115
The stages with the
transmutation process

356
00:16:41,115 --> 00:16:42,548
are construction, deconstruction,

357
00:16:42,548 --> 00:16:44,182
and reconstruction...

358
00:16:44,182 --> 00:16:47,682
This guy just must stop
at the deconstruction phase.

359
00:16:47,682 --> 00:16:50,048
But if Scar is
an alchemist as well...

360
00:16:50,048 --> 00:16:51,415
doesn't that mean
he's strayed from

361
00:16:51,415 --> 00:16:53,682
whatever his
'ways of God' are, too?

362
00:16:53,682 --> 00:16:55,182
[IMPACT]

363
00:16:55,782 --> 00:16:57,482
And what would
be his reasons for only

364
00:16:57,482 --> 00:17:00,248
targeting alchemists
with state certification?

365
00:17:07,315 --> 00:17:09,348
[SCAR THINKS] He's unusually
coordinated for his size,

366
00:17:09,348 --> 00:17:11,515
and his strength is
almost superhuman...

367
00:17:11,515 --> 00:17:13,448
That, combined
with his alchemy...

368
00:17:13,448 --> 00:17:15,248
He won't be an easy one.

369
00:17:17,115 --> 00:17:19,182
I have you cornered, Scar.

370
00:17:19,182 --> 00:17:19,848
[SCAR THINKS]
But there's a moment

371
00:17:19,848 --> 00:17:21,748
when his swing is too wide.

372
00:17:21,748 --> 00:17:23,382
There it is!

373
00:17:26,115 --> 00:17:28,115
[GUN SHOTS]

374
00:17:30,815 --> 00:17:31,782
You get him?

375
00:17:31,782 --> 00:17:34,748
He's too fast.
I only grazed him with one shot.

376
00:17:38,121 --> 00:17:39,787
Red eyes, and brown skin.

377
00:17:39,787 --> 00:17:41,621
That means he's--

378
00:17:41,621 --> 00:17:43,954
Of course! He's an Ishvalan!

379
00:17:46,721 --> 00:17:48,087
Perhaps there are too many...

380
00:17:48,087 --> 00:17:49,921
You might as well give up, Scar.

381
00:17:49,921 --> 00:17:51,954
You're not getting away...

382
00:17:52,187 --> 00:17:54,187
[IMPACT BLAST]

383
00:17:54,187 --> 00:17:56,221
[CRIES OF PANIC FROM SOLDIERS]

384
00:17:59,921 --> 00:18:01,621
[HAVOC]
Bastard is in the sewers.

385
00:18:01,621 --> 00:18:02,621
[ROY
Stay put.

386
00:18:02,621 --> 00:18:05,021
[HAVOC] Sure. You don't
have to tell me twice.

387
00:18:05,021 --> 00:18:07,187
Sorry Armstrong...
but thank you for

388
00:18:07,187 --> 00:18:10,654
buying us enough time
to surround him.

389
00:18:10,654 --> 00:18:12,154
I was hardly buying time.

390
00:18:12,154 --> 00:18:15,021
It was all I could do to
keep myself from being killed.

391
00:18:15,021 --> 00:18:16,721
Oh! Is it
over now?

392
00:18:16,721 --> 00:18:19,221
Lt. Colonel Hughes, where have
you been this whole time?

393
00:18:19,221 --> 00:18:21,087
I thought it
best to lay low.

394
00:18:21,087 --> 00:18:23,287
[ROY] You didn't think about
maybe backing us up?!

395
00:18:23,287 --> 00:18:24,287
Of course not!

396
00:18:24,287 --> 00:18:25,254
A person like me shouldn't
get dragged into a

397
00:18:25,254 --> 00:18:27,921
freak show with you
pack of pseudo humans!

398
00:18:27,921 --> 00:18:29,187
It's bad for
my health...!

399
00:18:29,187 --> 00:18:30,054
Don't just stand there!

400
00:18:30,054 --> 00:18:31,587
We've got things to do!

401
00:18:31,587 --> 00:18:32,554
[HUGHES]
Deploy troops!

402
00:18:32,554 --> 00:18:33,887
Circulate his description!

403
00:18:33,887 --> 00:18:35,087
[SOLDIERS]
Yes sir!

404
00:18:35,087 --> 00:18:37,021
Oh no, Alphonse!

405
00:18:37,021 --> 00:18:38,521
Alphonse!

406
00:18:40,054 --> 00:18:43,121
Al! Talk to me!
Are you all right?

407
00:18:43,121 --> 00:18:46,054
That suit of armor is
Elric's younger brother, is it?

408
00:18:46,054 --> 00:18:49,021
There's gotta be a really
long story behind this one.

409
00:18:49,021 --> 00:18:50,754
[ED] Come on, Al!
Al, do you hear me?

410
00:18:50,754 --> 00:18:52,154
[AL PUNCHES ED]

411
00:18:52,154 --> 00:18:54,287
[AL] Why didn't you run away
when I told you to?

412
00:18:54,287 --> 00:18:55,954
What kind of idiot are you?

413
00:18:55,954 --> 00:18:58,321
No way! I'm not just gonna
run away and leave you behind.

414
00:18:58,321 --> 00:19:00,854
Which is exactly
why you're an idiot?

415
00:19:02,187 --> 00:19:03,954
What do you keep
punching me like that for?

416
00:19:03,954 --> 00:19:04,887
If I'd run away,

417
00:19:04,887 --> 00:19:06,554
you could've been killed,
you know that?!

418
00:19:06,554 --> 00:19:08,154
[AL] And maybe
I wouldn't have been...!

419
00:19:08,154 --> 00:19:11,654
Making the decision to die
is something only an idiot does!

420
00:19:11,654 --> 00:19:13,154
Hey, easy on the idiot stuff!

421
00:19:13,154 --> 00:19:15,021
I'm still your
older brother, got it?!

422
00:19:15,021 --> 00:19:18,021
[AL]
I'll say it all I want to.

423
00:19:18,021 --> 00:19:20,087
[AL]
Survival is the only way, Ed...

424
00:19:20,087 --> 00:19:22,721
Live on, learn
more about alchemy...

425
00:19:22,721 --> 00:19:24,687
You could find a way
to get our bodies back

426
00:19:24,687 --> 00:19:26,287
and help people like Nina...

427
00:19:26,287 --> 00:19:28,721
You can't do that by dying!

428
00:19:28,721 --> 00:19:31,221
[AL] I won't allow you to
abandon the possibility of hope

429
00:19:31,221 --> 00:19:34,887
and choose a meaningless death!

430
00:19:34,887 --> 00:19:36,254
[AL]
Oh great...!

431
00:19:36,254 --> 00:19:37,887
And now my arm's come off

432
00:19:37,887 --> 00:19:40,187
because my brother's
a big, fat idiot!

433
00:19:43,754 --> 00:19:46,821
We're really falling apart...
aren't we, Brother?

434
00:19:46,821 --> 00:19:50,054
We look like we
belong in a junkyard.

435
00:19:51,054 --> 00:19:53,721
But we're still alive.

436
00:19:53,721 --> 00:19:55,021
We are.

437
00:19:56,021 --> 00:19:57,554
Good grief. I've
stumbled into an

438
00:19:57,554 --> 00:19:59,787
extra special kind
of freak show, huh?

439
00:19:59,787 --> 00:20:01,754
Yeah, sorry.

440
00:20:01,754 --> 00:20:05,121
Don't worry, I won't
tell anyone upstairs...

441
00:20:05,121 --> 00:20:07,887
[HUGHES] If this got out,
things would get complicated.

442
00:20:07,887 --> 00:20:10,754
[ROY] Yeah... The older brother
aside, I wouldn't even

443
00:20:10,754 --> 00:20:13,221
know how to explain the
younger brother's body.

444
00:20:15,921 --> 00:20:17,721
I don't envy you...

445
00:20:17,721 --> 00:20:21,254
[HUGHES] This is one tough
customer you're dealing with.

446
00:20:21,254 --> 00:20:23,287
And now we know he's Ishvalan.

447
00:20:30,321 --> 00:20:32,087
[ROY] The Ishvalans
were a race of people

448
00:20:32,087 --> 00:20:33,987
who lived to the east of us...

449
00:20:33,987 --> 00:20:35,954
They believed that their
god Ishvala was the one,

450
00:20:35,954 --> 00:20:38,054
absolute creator.

451
00:20:38,054 --> 00:20:40,287
Even after they were
annexed into the country,

452
00:20:40,287 --> 00:20:43,054
there were still conflicts
between us and them...

453
00:20:43,054 --> 00:20:45,221
Then, thirteen years ago,

454
00:20:45,221 --> 00:20:47,087
a military officer
accidentally shot

455
00:20:47,087 --> 00:20:49,087
and killed an Ishvalan child...

456
00:20:49,087 --> 00:20:51,821
And that led to
a full-blown civil war.

457
00:20:51,821 --> 00:20:52,921
[GUNFIRE]

458
00:20:55,654 --> 00:20:58,187
[ROY] One uprising led to
another, and before long,

459
00:20:58,187 --> 00:21:01,287
the rebellion had spread
to the whole eastern sector.

460
00:21:01,287 --> 00:21:03,087
After seven years of this...

461
00:21:03,087 --> 00:21:03,887
an order came down

462
00:21:03,887 --> 00:21:06,654
from the military
high-command...

463
00:21:07,654 --> 00:21:10,721
...to exterminate Ishval.

464
00:21:10,721 --> 00:21:11,821
Many State Alchemists were

465
00:21:11,821 --> 00:21:14,287
brought in to act
as human weapons.

466
00:21:16,754 --> 00:21:21,021
[PANIC AND SCREAMING]

467
00:21:22,254 --> 00:21:23,687
[ROY] Needless to say...

468
00:21:23,687 --> 00:21:27,154
the State Alchemists
produced striking results.

469
00:21:27,154 --> 00:21:29,754
That man is an
Ishvalan survivor.

470
00:21:29,754 --> 00:21:32,821
In a sense, his
revenge is justified.

471
00:21:32,821 --> 00:21:33,921
No way!

472
00:21:33,921 --> 00:21:36,887
There's no justification
for taking revenge on people

473
00:21:36,887 --> 00:21:38,687
who had nothing
to do with it...!

474
00:21:38,687 --> 00:21:40,887
He's just dressing his
ugly lust for vengeance

475
00:21:40,887 --> 00:21:42,187
in the mantle of his God and

476
00:21:42,187 --> 00:21:44,621
calling himself
an agent of justice.

477
00:21:44,621 --> 00:21:48,621
Still, the fact is, he's coming
at us with full force...

478
00:21:48,621 --> 00:21:51,321
We can't let ourselves
be killed for his cause.

479
00:21:51,321 --> 00:21:54,187
Next time there
will be no more talk.

480
00:21:54,187 --> 00:21:54,887
Got it?

481
00:21:54,887 --> 00:21:57,887
Yes sir!

482
00:21:57,887 --> 00:21:59,587
Well Ed, Alphonse...

483
00:21:59,587 --> 00:22:01,687
what are you two
going to do now...?

484
00:22:01,687 --> 00:22:03,521
What's the plan?

485
00:22:04,587 --> 00:22:06,221
We're going to
keep moving...

486
00:22:06,221 --> 00:22:07,621
We can't just sit around,

487
00:22:07,621 --> 00:22:09,854
not as long
as we're still alive.

488
00:22:09,854 --> 00:22:11,221
Brother...

489
00:22:11,221 --> 00:22:12,954
Before we can make
any headway on getting

490
00:22:12,954 --> 00:22:15,887
your body back, we have
to get my arm back to normal

491
00:22:15,887 --> 00:22:18,154
[ED] After all, I'm the only
one who knows how to

492
00:22:18,154 --> 00:22:20,087
bond your soul to the armor.

493
00:22:20,087 --> 00:22:21,987
[AL] Uh-huh.

494
00:22:21,987 --> 00:22:23,987
We've got no choice.

495
00:22:23,987 --> 00:22:25,787
[ED]
It's been a long time...

496
00:22:25,787 --> 00:22:28,287
But we need to pay a
visit to our mechanic.

497
00:24:04,721 --> 00:24:06,654
<i>[NARRATOR] In order to repair
their injured bodies,</i>

498
00:24:06,654 --> 00:24:07,521
<i>Ed and Al set off</i>

499
00:24:07,521 --> 00:24:09,587
<i>for their former
home in Resembool,</i>

500
00:24:09,587 --> 00:24:10,554
<i>where they are met</i>

501
00:24:10,554 --> 00:24:12,687
<i>by their mechanics,
